18. Qa4+ { 18.Rd1!? } 18... Kf8
{ 18...Bd7  19.Qb3  Bf5  Thanks to this little maneuver our queen is slightly closer to the kingside in case we need her majesty via c2 or d1.  20.O-O  O-O  21.Bxh5  .   If  19...f5  20.O-O-O  Ne5  21.Kb1  O-O  22.Rd2  .  If  21...Rc8  22.c5  . }
19. O-O Ne5 20. Rad1
{ We activate our Rooks on the center and we will prepare c5 to have some freedom on the Queen side. }
20... Bg4 { 20...Re8  21.c5  dxc5  22.Nxe4  Bxe4  23.Qxe4   20...Rd8  21.Rd4 }
21. Bxg4 hxg4 22. Nxe4 Qxc4 23. Qxc4 Nxc4 24. Bf4
{ All our pieces are in active positions and they will be improved very fast while Black will have a lot of passive pieces. }
