10... O-O 11. O-O-O b6 12. Bd3 Bb7
{ After this we get into a long forcing line that gives White a winning advantage. If  12...Qe7?  Qe4  wins.   If  12...Bd7  Nf3  gives White an advantage. The Rook is attacking through a discovery and we quickly get to hit the h7-pawn as well. }
13. Bxh7+
{ After this unexpected sacrifice, all White's pieces become active very quickly. }
13... Kxh7 14. Ne4 Nd4
{ Another tempo!  14...Qe7  15.Ng5  Kh6  16.Qh4  Kg6  17.Qh7  Kf6   17...Kxg5  18.f4  Kxf4  19.Qh5+-  18.Ne4  Ke5  19.f4  Checkmate is coming!  ...Kxf4  20.Rhf1  Ke5  21.Qxg7  Kxe4   21...f6  22.Qg3  Kxe4  23.Qf4  22.Qg4  Ke5  23.Qf4  . }
15. cxd4 Bxe4 16. Qxe4+ Kg8 17. dxc5 Qg5+ 18. Qe3
{ This Rook ending with a pawn up is easily winning. } *

