10. O-O-O h5
{ It's hard to believe that another pawn push is going to be the right move. However, it's not so easy to refute. }
11. Nde2
{ We remove the Knight from d4 to boost the f4 push and leave the d-file to the Queen. }
11... Bh6 12. f4 Nf6 13. Kb1 { Starting to clear the c1-h6 diagonal. } 13...
O-O 14. Qd6 Qxd6 15. Rxd6 exf4 16. Nxf4
{ We take with the Knight in order to get a faster development for the Bishop. }
16... Bxf4 { 16...Nxe4  17.Nxe4  Bxe4  18.Nxh5± } 17. Rxf6 Bxg3 18. Rxb6 Bxh2
19. Rxb7 Bg3 20. a4
{ With a very comfortable endgame thanks to our piece activity. } *

