[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3) Sicilian with 2...Nc6 and 4.d5"]
[Black "Sicilian, 2.Nf3 Nc6 … 6.Be3 Nf6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 d5
{ A dangerous line if we don't know it. However, it loses a lot of its value once we are sure how to deal with it. }
5. exd5
{ Forcing the Queen to the center in order to win some tempi on it later on. }
5... Qxd5 6. Be3 { We just develop and prepare the tempo-winning Nc3. } 6...
Nf6
{ This doesn't stop the tempo-winning Nc3 and gives us an excellent position.   6...e5  7.Nc3  Bb4  8.Nb5+-  Too many weaknesses and too little development – Black's position doesn't hold. }
7. Nc3 Qd8 8. Nxc6 Qxd1+ 9. Rxd1 bxc6 10. Be2
{ With a nice edge thanks to our structure and piece activity. We'll play Bf3 and O-O next. }
*

