{ Having …Bb4 available is important to avoid losing more development tempi.   6...Nxd4  7.Nc3!  developing with tempo!  Nf3  8.Qxf3!  without compromising our structure  Qxf3  9.gxf3+-  . }
7. Nc3 { A development and tempo-winning move. } 7... Bb4 8. Qd3
{ 8.Qg4  is the known alternative, which also offers a nice advantage. However, there are not so many games with Qd3 and is even a bit stronger.   We are preparing long castle and preventing the doubling of pawns. We place the Queen on d3 and not Qd2 so that we can unpin when castling long. }
8... Nf6 9. a3 Qa5
{ With this pin, Black somewhat delays taking on c3 and almost makes sure to double our c-pawns. }
10. Nxc6
{ This moves s us a long-term better structure by creating three pawn islands. }
10... bxc6 11. O-O-O Be7
{ Black needs to stay away from the endgame arising after Bxc3 and play this unbalanced position instead.   11...Bxc3  12.Qxc3  Qxc3  13.bxc3  with the Bishop pair heading for the endgame. }
12. Qc4
{ Puting pressure on the c6-square while freeing the way for our Rook and Bishop. }
12... O-O 13. Qxc6 Bd7 14. Qa6
{ 14.Rxd7?!  Nxd7  15.Qxd7  Bxa3!  and Black is slightly better. } 14... Qc7
15. Rd4 Rfd8 16. Rc4 Qe5 17. Bd3
{ All our pieces are perfectly protecting each other, we have no weaknesses and our extra pawn is really healthy. }
*

