{ We have reached the initial position of the Lowenthal Sicilian. Black tries to justify all his weaknesses and the pair of Bishops with a quick development.  It is dangerous if we don't know how to play it. }
6. Nd6+ Bxd6 7. Qxd6 Qf6
{ This is the most played line, Black tries to counterattack with …Qg6-Ne7-d5 and they have some tricks after that with …Nb4.   However, if we are careful enough we could avoid them all with an edge. }
8. Qd2
{ After analyzing plenty of possibilities I ended up concluding that Qd2 with the b3 plans that I am going to recommend is the best possibility against this line, and moreover, it is not very known. }
8... Nge7 { One of the most normal continuations. We will stick to our plan. }
9. Nc3 O-O 10. b3 { We plan to develop our Bishop via a3 or b2. } *

