9... Nge7 10. Bd3
{ Now we stop Black's …d5 move and we can go on with out development. } 10...
d6 11. b3 { Our scheme is the same, Black can't stop our ideal setup. } 11...
O-O 12. Nc3
{ We don't know yet where to develop our Bishop, so we will choose at the last moment depending on Black's move order. }
12... Nb4 13. Ba3 { Putting the Bishop in the best diagonal. } 13... Nxd3+ 14.
Qxd3 Qxg2 15. O-O-O
{ Our King is extremely safe and with the g-file open we have a great position. }
