{ Once more sidestep that protects our Bishop. } 9... Bc5 10. O-O Nxd5 11. Nf5
{ This is what happens when you don't develop fast. } 11... O-O
{ This fails because of a concrete line. } 12. Qxd5 Bxb5 13. Qxc5 Bxf1 14. Nc3
{ We gain control over d1 while developing one of our last pieces. } 14... Ba6
15. Bh6 { Blowing up the castle! } 15... gxh6 16. Qe5
{ Now our Queen can keep provovking new weaknesses. } 16... f6 17. Qg3+ Kf7 18.
Rd1
{ With excellent piece coordination and a Black King with a lot of trouble. } *

