{ The Rook is hinting threats to the King on g8. We have other ideas like f5+f6, and then the Rook can swing to h3 via g3.   There it will guard the 3rd rank once our Bishop drops to c1 and then all our pieces will be perfectly coordinated both in attack and defense. }
16... Bb7 17. Rg3 Bc6
{ Opening up the b-file and looking for …Ba4 ideas.   17...Rfc8  18.f5  exf5  19.Qxf5  Ne5  20.Qf2  Bc6  21.Bb6  Qb8  22.Ba5 }
18. Rh3
{ A very concrete move to attack Black's King. There is no good defense: Black has to move the f8-Rook to allow …Nf8 if necessary. }
18... Rab8 { This doesn't allow …Nf8. } 19. f5 Nxc2 20. Qh5 h6
{ 20...Na3  21.Kc1+- } 21. gxh6
{ Black is not even close to put up with the upcoming piece avalanche. } *

