21. Nxc2 Nxe4 22. Bxf7+ Kh8 { 22...Kf8  23.Nd5!  Qd7  24.g6+- } 23. Nd5
{ An extremely complex move, the only way to win here: we are removing the b7-Bishop to get full control of the light squares and stop all tricks on the Queen on f3.   23...Nxg3  24.Qxg3  Bxd5  25.Bxd5+-   23...Bxd5  24.Bxd5  Rxb2??  A last desperate attempt. Next comes quite a long and somewhat scary sequence, but no big deal.  25.Kxb2  Qc3  26.Kc1  Rc8  27.Bxe4  fxe4  28.Qg2+-  d5   28...Qa3  29.Kd2  Qa5  30.Ke2  Rxc2  31.Bd2  and we finally find some shelter among our pieces.  29.Bd4?  Ba3  30.Kb1  Rb8  31.Ka2  Rb2  32.Ka1+-  That's what I meant by scary: it's a miracle, but everything is perfectly secured and there's not much Black can do, other than deliver a couple of checks and then resign. }
*

