[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "9) O'Kelly"]
[Black "O'Kelly: 2.Nf3 a6 3.c4 Nc6 4.d4 5.Nxd4 e5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 a6
{ With this move, we enter the O'Kelly Variation. Black's idea is to answer  3.d4  cxd4  Nxd4  Nf6  Nc3  e5  , when it is considered that Black just equalizes. }
3. c4
{ Since Black's 2…a6 didn't fight for the center, we'll use our turn to set up some kind of Maroczy bind.   In general, we'll wait for Black to play …Nc6 before we break on d4, since the Black Knight is usually better placed on d7 in Hedgehog setups. }
3... Nc6
{ Usually this is not an ideal square for the Knight in these structures. } 4.
d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 e5
{ Quite weakening. However, it will all become weirdly concrete. } 6. Nf5 d6 7.
Nc3 g6 8. Ne3 Be6 9. Bd3
{ This position is similar to my recommendation against the Kalashnikov system, but we have some extra tempi. }
*

