{ Since Black's 2…a6 didn't fight for the center, we'll use our turn to set up some kind of Maroczy bind.   In general, we'll wait for Black to play …Nc6 before we break on d4, since the Black Knight is usually better placed on d7 in Hedgehog setups. }
3... Nc6
{ Usually this is not an ideal square for the Knight in these structures. } 4.
d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 e5
{ Quite weakening. However, it will all become weirdly concrete. } 6. Nf5 d5 7.
cxd5 Bxf5 8. exf5 Nd4 9. Nc3 { 9...Nf6  transposes to a line we'll see later. }
9... Ne7 10. Bd3 { Developing a piece and looking for a quick castle. } 10...
Nexf5 11. O-O Bc5 12. Re1
{ We enjoy a nice edge thanks to the Bishop pair and the weakness of e5. } *

