{ An interesting attempt to unbalance the position.   7...d6  8.Ne3 } 8. cxd5
Bxf5 9. exf5 Nd4 10. Bd3 { Defense and development. } 10... Nxd5
{ The most common, but inaccurate, as we are going to see. } 11. O-O
{ We don't care about Black taking on c3, since that would take the d4 square away from their Knight. }
11... Bb4 12. Be4 { Putting more pressure on the d5-Knight. } 12... Bxc3 13.
Bxd5 { Keeping the attack on the Bishop. } 13... Bxb2 14. Bxf7+
