{ 22...Rf8   22...h6  23.Rbe1!!  The pawn takes the square away from the King.  23.Rb6  Rf6  The beginning of the show: White's Queen maneuvers to b1.  24.Qd3  Kh6  25.Qd2  Kg6  26.Qc2  Kh6  27.Qc1  Kg6  28.Qb1  Kh6  29.Rf5!!  There is no back-rank mate thanks to the Queen on b1.  Qxf5  30.Qxf5  Rxb6  31.Qh3  Kg6   31...Kg5  32.Qe3++-  32.Qg3  Kh5!  Only square to avoid dropping the Rook.  33.Qd3!!  We are threatening to invade on h7, as well as a series of checks to pick up the b6-Rook.  33...Rg6   33...Rc6  34.Qxh7  Kg5  35.Qxg7  Kf5  36.h4+-  With a winning endgame. Of course, there is no need to memorize all this stuff, but knowing there is such a forcing line is useful.  34.Qf5  Rg5   34...Kh6  25.g4+-  35.Qh3  Kg6  36.Qe6  Kh5  37.h4+- }
23. Qf7+ Kh6 24. Rb3
{ The Rook is coming to deliver a certain checkmate with no defense for Black. }
