[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 a6
{ With this move, we enter the O'Kelly Variation. Black's idea is to answer  3.d4  cxd4  Nxd4  Nf6  Nc3  e5  , when it is considered that Black just equalizes. }
3. c4
{ Since Black's 2…a6 didn't fight for the center, we'll use our turn to set up some kind of Maroczy bind.   In general, we'll wait for Black to play …Nc6 before we break on d4, since the Black Knight is usually better placed on d7 in Hedgehog setups. }
3... d6 4. d4
{ Here we can't delay d4, since Black was threatening …e5 closing the center.   In any case, Black will get an inferior Hedgehog: due to the early …d6, …Bb4 will never be threatened and White doesn't need to burn a tempo on a3. }
4... Bg4 5. dxc5 Qa5+ 6. Nc3 { Protecting our King while developing a piece. }
6... Qxc5 7. Be3 { Another piece comes with tempo! } 7... Qa5 8. Qb3
{ White's development lead is just crushing. } *

