{ Since Black's 2…a6 didn't fight for the center, we'll use our turn to set up some kind of Maroczy bind.   In general, we'll wait for Black to play …Nc6 before we break on d4, since the Black Knight is usually better placed on d7 in Hedgehog setups. }
3... e6 4. Nc3
{ We are not in a hurry to play d4 as long as Black is not really threatening …e5. }
4... Qc7 5. Be2
{ Black is not threatening neither …e5 nor …Nd4 yet. Therefore, we are not in a hurry to play d4, and then moves such as …Bb4 won't be possible. }
5... d6 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4
{ We'll end up transposing to a well-known position. } *

