{ Even though at first sight the e7-Bishop might look a worse piece than our d5-Knight, in the long run this trade will benefit us because our b1-Knight is going to replace it and later on d6 may end up being a weakness.   Also, we gain the Bishop pair and the d4-square will be easily guarded by a Bishop on e3. These are the positional guidelines.   However, we must take into account that in similar positions Nxe7 might not be the best move if Black could potentially generate some counterplay against the c4-pawn.   That's not the case here and Nxe7 offers a pleasant edge. }
9... Qxe7 10. Nc3 Be6 11. Be3 Rc8 12. Be2
{ This basic setup is good for White. We will castle King-side and then win more space with f3-b3 }
*

