{ The main alternative to 6...e6, forcing us to do something with the well-positioned d4-Knight and difficulting the c1-Bishop's development.  Black is ready to play the resulting structure after Nxc6 and this is what we are going to do. Initially, I was going to recommend 7.Nb3, but after quite a deep analysis I realized Black is close to equal and it is too big a memory effort just to get a similar or worse position than after 7.Nxc6. }
