1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6
{ The Classical Sicilian, certainly one of the trickiest and hard to understand. One of its perks is its flexibility: Black can play ...e5, ...e6, or even ...g6 Dragon-style. Recently it has become more popular and currently, it is one of the most played in open tournaments. }
6. Bc4
{ Again, my recommendation will be somewhat unexpected for our opponents. Most of them will be used to the more usual  6.Bg5  and our idea is basically to look for Be3+Qe2+O-O-O and prepare a kingside attack. }
6... e6 { Once e6 is played, Ng4 is off the cards. Therefore, we start with }
7. Be3 { Finishing development. } 7... Be7
{ The main move by far. However, it strikes as not the most accurate and actually we can obtain quite a comfortable edge against it. In this move order we are in time to castle long without issues }
8. Qe2
{ The best square for the Queen, where it controls g4 and allows the rook to set up Nxc6+e5 ideas }
8... O-O { 8...a6  Transposes to the  7...a6  8.Qe2  Be7  move-order. } 9.
O-O-O Qc7
{ It's very natural to move the Queen away from the d-file, but a little slow nevertheless. }
10. Rhg1
{ Adding power to the g4+g5 thrust. The Rook on d1 is still well placed. }
10... a6
{ Most typical Black counterplay   10...Na5  11.Bd3  helps us reroute the Bishop to a promising diagonal. }
11. g4 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 b5
{ 12...e5  13.Be3  Bxg4??  counting on the looseness of the c4-Bishop, but it fails.  14.Rxg4  Nxg4  15.Nd5  crushing intermetzzo. Black has no way of defend e7 and still hit c4, so  15...Qd8  16.Nxe7+  Qxe7  17.Qxg4+- }
13. g5 Nd7 14. Nd5
{ A crushing strike based on the strength of our Bishop on the a2-f7 diagonal. }
14... exd5
{ The most critical, but the worst.   14...Qd8  15.Nxe7+  Qxe7  16.Bb3±  Is a moral defeat for Black. We keep the bishop pair which strengthens our plan of pushing our kingside. }
15. Bxd5 Rb8 16. g6
{ For example:   16...Nf6  17.gxh7+  Kh8  18.Rxg7  Kxg7  19.Rg1  Kh8  20.Qh5  and due to the pin, Black can't do anything about Qg5.     16...Ne5   16...Bf6  17.Qh5  it's the same  17.Qh5  hxg6  18.Rxg6  Bf6  19.Bxe5!!  eliminating the defender  19...Bxe5  20.Rdg1  and there's no avoiding Qh6+Rxg7. }
*

