15. Bxd5 Bb7 { The best defense, challenging the powerful Bishop. } 16. g6
{ Making use of the pin on the f7-pawn to open everything up } 16... Bf6 17.
Qh5
{ Here comes the most important attacker!     17...Rfc8  18.Qxh7+  Kf8  19.Bb3+-  The Bishop on b3 protects everything perfectly well and the Black king is not going to survive the upcoming slaughter. }
17... h6 18. gxf7+ Kh7
{ 18...Kh8  19.Rxg7!!+-  And checkmate cannot be prevented. } 19. Qg6+ Kh8 20.
Bxf6 { Winning the game. } *

