17... hxg6 18. Rxg6
{ The start of a forcing line which takes us to a winning endgame. } 18... Bxd5
{ The most sensible . } 19. Rxg7+ Bxg7 20. Bxg7 Qxc2+
{ A desperate resource to get kingside defenders in time.   20...f6  21.Rg1+-  followed by a deadly discover check. }
21. Kxc2 Bxe4+ 22. Kd2 Kxg7 23. Qg4+ Bg6 24. Qxd7
{ Black can still put up some fight, but the position is actually lost. The strongest plan is to push f5 while keeping our King safe. }
24... Rh8 25. Ke1
{ Aditionally, a6 is a weakness that could help us create a queenside passer too. }
