{ Defending e4 and avoiding that b5 hits the Bishop. We are threatening g4. }
11... Qc7
{ Sidestepping from  11...b5  12.Nxb5  axb5  13.Bxb5+-  winning the Queen. }
12. g4 b5 13. g5 Nd7 14. f4
{ Again, we are quite faster than Black thanks to this precise order which stops the direct b5. }
