11. Bd3
{ Defending e4 and avoiding that b5 hits the Bishop. We are threatening g4. }
11... b5 { But Black can go for this anyway! } 12. Nxb5
{ The key. We need to be a bit careful since we're opening up the b-file for Black. However, it's not objectively enough. }
12... O-O 13. Nc3 { The Knight was already under attack. } 13... Bd7
{ It's important to bring all the pieces.   13...Nd7  14.f4  controlling e5 but preparing f5. }
14. Kb1
{ There are different defensive setups: mainly, either Ka1+Rb1 or play  15.b3  and be ready to answer  15...a5  with  16.a4  to tuck a piece on b5. We can combine this with a kingside attack. }
14... Rab8 { 14...Rfb8  15.Bd2  a5  16.Ka1± } 15. Bd2 Rfc8 16. b3 a5
{ 16...Qc5  17.Rhe1  simply pushing e5. } 17. a4
{ With material advantage and Black's attack is not making progress. } *

