{ After this forcing sequence we reach this complicated position where we have a large advantage. Our king is quite safe thanks to the b3-bishop and b2 is an additional layer of protection. Our pieces are better coordinated thanks to our king being castled, so next, we'll harass the g7-bishop. }
16... Nxb3 17. axb3 a5 18. e5 d5 { 18...a4  19.Qg2+- } 19. Kxb2
{ We take now that the g7-Bishop is shut down and there are enough pieces around our king to make sure it won't suffer. }
*

