{ Black uses the fact that we can’t play c3, as that would cut off our rook along the 3rd rank }
26. Qe7 Re8
{ 26...Qf7  27.Qxf7+  Kxf7  28.c3±  With two pawns and huge piece activity, this is a very comfortable endgame. }
27. Qxb7 Qh5
{ 27...Re1  28.Qb8++-   27...Be4  28.f3  Bxc2  29.Qb4±  With full control. We are ready to push the d-pawn further. }
28. h3 Rf6
{ Basically, if our opponent knows everything so far, he deserves a merely slightly worse endgame. }
29. Qb4 Qd1 30. Ne5 Bxc2 { 30...Rxe5  31.Qb8+ } 31. Nd3 f3
{ This just creates a weakness on f3 for the endgame. } 32. g3 Bxd3 33. Rxd3
Qc1 34. d6 Re1 35. Qxe1 Qxe1 36. d7
{ Again the same endgame, but now with a pawn on f3 added to the weakness on a6. }
