11. Bxc4 Qxc4 12. Qf3 { Hoping for g4 directly. } 12... b5
{ Seeking to misplace the knight on c3. The main fight is on the d5 square or, in the case of Black, the break and therefore both the knight on c3 and f6 are extremely important. }
13. a3 a5 14. g4 b4
{ Black tries to save a tempo on  14...h6  but it doesn't work. } 15. axb4
{ 15...Qxb4  16.g5+-  is too slow. } 15... d5 16. Nd2 Qxb4 17. Nxd5 Nxd5 18.
exd5 Qxb2 19. d6
{ Surprise, surprise! The Rook is inmmune and, again, Black's King is in a lot of trouble. }
19... Qxa1+
{ 19...Rd8  20.Rb1+-  and our Rooks will use all the open lines in the queenside. }
20. Ke2
{ Black needs to surrender their Queen but their underdevelopment and the strong d6-pawn ensures that we are completely winning. }
*

