6... e5
{ The main move these days. Black gains space in the center and moves our strong Knight away from the center. The game will center around the weak d5-square: they'd love to achieve d6-d5, but for the moment we have a better grip over it. }
7. Nb3 Be6 8. Be3 Nbd7
{ Interesting move order rather little tested. It is not as easy as it seems to transpose to the other line that we want to play because after   9.O-O  Be7  10.Qd3  there is  10...Rc8  and  11.Nd5  is not good because of  11...Bxd5  12.exd5  Nb6  with counterplay against d5.   Obviously, there are other moves but I preferred to recommend something quite concrete against this line. }
9. f4
{ Again we are looking for concrete lines. Black must now decide whether to take on f4 or allow f5. }
