{ The main move as Black doesn't want to be crushed under the weight of our kingside pawns. }
10. Bxf4 Ne5 11. Qd4 Qc7 12. Qa4+
{ With this precise check we get rid of that annoying Bishop on e6. } 12... Bd7
{ 12...Nfd7  13.Nd4± } 13. Bb5
{ Without these two bishops, both the d5 and f5 weaknesses are more significant. }
13... Be7 14. Bxd7+ Qxd7 15. Qxd7+
{ With a very comfortable endgame. We have a space advantage and better squares for our pieces. }
