{ The line with more games follows with  14.Bf3  However, after a lot of analysis, I ended up concluding that Black equalizes very comfortably after  14...Bd6  15.Bg5  h6  16.Bh4  b5  17.b3  c4! }
14. c4 Bd6 15. f3 { 15.g3  hoping to transpose. } 15... Re8
{ 15...Nh5  16.g3  f5  17.Bd2± } 16. Qf5 g6
{ 16...e4  17.f4±  Black's pieces are becoming less active. } 17. Qg5
{ With the bishop pair and space advantage. } *

