13... Bg5 14. a5
{ We are in no hurry to take on g5 as this would improve Black's Queen. We will continue with c4 and Black will run out of useful moves. }
14... Rc8 15. c4
{ The pawn here is perfectly positioned because of the e2-bishop, so we don't have to worry about it. }
15... f5 { 15...Bxe3  16.Qxe3±  followed by Nd2+b4. } 16. f4
{ My favorite move. When the knight is on b3, we try to win the square d4, from where it will be very annoying.   16.Bxg5  Qxg5  17.Nd2  is an interesting attempt at transposition since Black does not have much more than g6* there. }
16... exf4 17. Bxf4 Bxf4 18. Rxf4 g6 19. Nd4 Ng7 20. b4
{ The space advantage is very noticeable. Black's position, while solid, is very restrained. }
